text: Abdur Rasheed Biswas (died 1991) was a Bangladeshi politician. He was elected as MP of Jessore-10 in the first general election of Bangladesh. He lived in Khalia village of what is now Mohammadpur Upazila of Magura District. He died on 11 December 1991. ==References== Category:Awami League politicians Category:People from Magura District Category:1st Jatiya Sangsad members Category:Bengali politicians Category:1991 deaths
